{"author":"Iso Tester","data":{"body":"## Completion verification ‚Äî PASS\n\nAll Acceptance Criteria and the Success Criterion are met. Every finding is grounded in tool output from the repository.\n\n---\n\n### Evidence base\n\n| File | Confirmed |\n|------|-----------|\n| `src/rebar/reducer/_managed_refs.py` | ‚úÖ full implementation: `add_managed_ref`, `seed_managed_refs_from_current`, `should_propagate_removal`, `serialize_managed_refs` |\n| `src/rebar/reducer/_processors.py` (lines 57‚Äì60, 246‚Äì248, 347‚Äì352, 529‚Äì543) | ‚úÖ folds `managed_refs` in `process_create`, `process_link`, `process_edit(parent_id)`; seeds in `process_snapshot` when key absent |\n| `src/rebar/reducer/_state.py` (line 28) | ‚úÖ `managed_refs: []` in `make_initial_state()` |\n| `tests/scripts/reducer/test_managed_refs.py` | ‚úÖ 10 tests including the compact-then-reconcile end-to-end test at lines 206‚Äì262 |\n| `tests/unit/rebar_reconciler/diffing/test_link_removal_sync.py` | ‚úÖ two-pass churn regression at lines 264‚Äì306 |\n| `tests/unit/rebar_reconciler/diffing/test_parent_detach_sync.py` | ‚úÖ parent detach gates on `managed_refs` |\n| `src/rebar/_engine/rebar_reconciler/outbound_differ.py` (lines 518, 526, 1126, 1166) | ‚úÖ `should_propagate_removal` imported and called for both parent and link paths |\n| `docs/managed-refs.md` | ‚úÖ full pattern documentation |\n\n---\n\n### Per-criterion verdicts\n\n**AC1 ‚Äî Reducer maintains `compiled_state.managed_refs` as strictly-monotonic, deterministically-sorted union‚Ä¶** ‚úÖ MET\n\n`add_managed_ref` (idempotent, monotonic, never removes) is called in: `process_create` at `_processors.py:60` for the initial `parent_id`; `process_link` at `_processors.py:248` for `(relation, resolved_target)`; `process_edit` at `_processors.py:351‚Äì352` when `field_name == \"parent_id\"`. `process_unlink` at `_processors.py:254` only filters `state[\"deps\"]` ‚Äî never touches `managed_refs`. `make_initial_state()` seeds the field as `[]` (preventing the `if field_name not in state: continue` guard from silently dropping the parent fold). Serialized via `serialize_managed_refs` ‚Üí `sorted(refs)` (deterministic).\n\n**AC2 ‚Äî Reducer seeds `managed_refs` from current deps + parent_id when absent; test proves pre-feature compacted ticket's existing refs become managed** ‚úÖ MET\n\n`process_snapshot` at `_processors.py:542‚Äì543` conditionally seeds via `seed_managed_refs_from_current(state)` when `\"managed_refs\" not in compiled_state`. `test_snapshot_without_managed_refs_is_seeded_from_current` (test file lines 127‚Äì147) writes a SNAPSHOT with no `managed_refs` key (simulating a pre-feature compacted ticket), reduces it, and asserts both the legacy `parent_id` and `deps` entries appear in `managed_refs`. The propagation chain is validated by `test_gate_propagates_only_managed_refs` ‚Äî a seeded ref causes `should_propagate_removal` to return `True`.\n\n**AC3 ‚Äî `managed_refs` survives `compact_ticket`; covered by a compact-then-reconcile test** ‚úÖ MET\n\n`test_unlink_after_compaction_still_propagates_removal` (test file lines 206‚Äì262) implements the full end-to-end chain the AC specifies:\n1. Reduces a real CREATE+LINK event log ‚Üí `managed_refs` carries `(\"blocks\", \"local-2\")`.\n2. Writes the resulting `compiled_state` as a SNAPSHOT into a new dir (simulating `compact_ticket`), then appends a POST-compaction UNLINK.\n3. Reduces the post-compaction dir ‚Üí `deps` is empty, `managed_refs` **still** carries the ref (monotonic through the compaction boundary).\n4. Calls `outbound_differ.compute_outbound_mutations()` over a Jira snapshot still carrying the link ‚Üí asserts that a link `action: remove` mutation is emitted.\n\nThis is the \"compact-then-reconcile\" chained test the AC explicitly calls for. The previous FAIL on this criterion was based on an older state of the file; the test is now present and non-skipped (no `skip`/`xfail` markers found).\n\n**AC4 ‚Äî SNAPSHOT byte-parity preserved (deterministic serialization; existing byte-parity guard passes)** ‚úÖ MET\n\n`serialize_managed_refs` returns `[[kind, target] for kind, target in sorted(refs)]` ‚Äî order is fully determined by content, not insertion order. `tests/interfaces/store/test_canonical_event_bytes.py` (line 39‚Äì77) exercises the full SNAPSHOT writer (compact-on-close) end-to-end, walking every committed event file and asserting `raw == canonical_bytes(parsed)`. The `managed_refs` field, initialized as `[]` in `make_initial_state()`, is included in any SNAPSHOT `compiled_state` and its sorted serialization makes it byte-stable.\n\n**AC5 ‚Äî Shared `should_propagate_removal` gate exists, provider-agnostic, defaults missing managed_refs to empty (False), unit-tested** ‚úÖ MET\n\n`should_propagate_removal(kind, target, local_ticket) -> bool` at `_managed_refs.py:139‚Äì152` contains no Jira-specific logic (operates only on normalized local `(kind, target)` pairs). Returns `False` when `managed_refs` is absent/empty/malformed (`parse_managed_refs` is tolerant by design at lines 60‚Äì78). `test_gate_propagates_only_managed_refs` (lines 187‚Äì194) and `test_gate_defaults_missing_managed_refs_to_no_removal` (lines 197‚Äì202) cover the REMOVE-vs-ADOPT decision and the empty/missing/malformed defaults respectively. Both parent (`outbound_differ.py:518,526`) and link (`outbound_differ.py:1126,1166`) paths import and call it.\n\n**AC6 ‚Äî Operator-facing regression: unlink a managed ref locally, run two reconcile passes, the ref stays removed** ‚úÖ MET\n\n`test_two_passes_managed_unlink_stays_removed` (test_link_removal_sync.py lines 264‚Äì306) drives a `_MutableJira` that reflects link deletes on subsequent reads. Pass 1: asserts the Jira link is deleted (`jira.issuelinks(\"PROJ-1\") == []`) and the inbound re-add is suppressed (`suppressed_1 >= 1`, `not adds_1`). Pass 2: over the refreshed snapshot (link now absent), asserts zero inbound link additions and the Jira side stays empty ‚Äî no resurrection, local `deps` stays empty. This is precisely the two-pass churn regression the AC specifies.\n\n**AC7 ‚Äî `docs/` documents the pattern (gate contract + `managed_refs` field + future reconcile-time reclamation hook)** ‚úÖ MET\n\n`docs/managed-refs.md` documents: `managed_refs` field semantics with fold points, monotonicity, and serialization (lines 37‚Äì87); the `should_propagate_removal` gate contract with signature, True/False semantics, and fail-open posture (lines 89‚Äì104); the future reclamation hook as an explicit out-of-scope item (lines 113‚Äì120); and the provider-extension template for new peers such as Linear/GitHub (lines 122‚Äì127).\n\n**Success Criterion ‚Äî Reusable, provider-agnostic primitive both parent and link removal sync consume, with no Jira-specific logic in the shared gate** ‚úÖ MET\n\n`should_propagate_removal` operates exclusively on local `(kind, target)` pairs. All Jira-specific resolution (Jira key ‚Üí local id) is performed by the caller (`_is_parent_managed_removal` at `outbound_differ.py:510‚Äì526`, `_diff_links_removal` at `outbound_differ.py:1118‚Äì1175`) before invoking the gate. The gate itself has no Jira imports or Jira-key logic.\n\n---\n\n### Summary\n\nAll seven Acceptance Criteria and the Success Criterion are met. The two criteria that caused prior FAIL verdicts are now satisfied:\n\n- **AC3**: `test_unlink_after_compaction_still_propagates_removal` (test_managed_refs.py lines 206‚Äì262) provides the required compact-then-reconcile chain: real event reduction ‚Üí SNAPSHOT ‚Üí post-compaction UNLINK ‚Üí reducer (managed_refs survives) ‚Üí outbound differ emits REMOVE.\n- **AC6**: `test_two_passes_managed_unlink_stays_removed` (test_link_removal_sync.py lines 264‚Äì306) provides the required two-pass operator regression using a mutable Jira fixture that reflects outbound deletes.\n\n**Verdict: PASS**"},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"COMMENT","timestamp":1782543143520903001,"uuid":"f8c1c60c-62dc-42f8-9682-8663ff4f994d"}